---
title: Mexican-Style Beef & Bean “Lasagna” 2x the delicious servings!
description: Get ready for a crowd-pleasing family style dinner that everyone (even the kiddos) will love: a magnificent mashup only our chefs could dream up “Mexican-style lasagna”: We replace the noodles with layers of flour tortillas, season the beef with Tex-Mex spices, add black beans, and sub in Mexican cheeses for mozzarella. Bake it so the flavors mingle in the oven, then straight to the table it goes with sour cream, crushed tortillas chips, hot sauce, and lime for customizable deliciousness.

This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64ca5572d1320bb7c7146b45-d16739fe.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64ca5572d1320bb7c7146b45.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 1000 kcal
  fat: 59 g
  saturated fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1640 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mexican-style-beef-and-bean-lasagna-64ca5572d1320bb7c7146b45
cuisine: Mexican
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{4}(trimmed), separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large, heavy-bottomed #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{20%oz}, scallion whites, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> If you don't have a pot that's big enough, use a large pan and work in batches.

While beef cooks, drain @black beans{1}. Halve @flour tortillas{6}.

Carefully drain any excess grease from pot.

> Use a slotted spoon to transfer beef to a bowl, then pour out grease and return beef to pot.

Stir in beans, @diced tomatoes{14%oz can}, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, and @chicken stock concentrate{3}. Cook, stirring constantly, until well combined, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Arrange four tortilla halves, cut sides facing out, on the bottom of a lightly oiled #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (use eight tortilla halves and a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} for 8 servings).

Spread one-third of the beef mixture in an even layer over tortillas, then top with one packet of @Mexican cheese blend{1.5%cup} (two packets for 8). Repeat two more times with remaining tortillas, beef mixture, and cheese.

Lightly coat a large piece of #aluminum foil{} with @nonstick cooking spray{}. Cover baking dish tightly with foil, coated side down. Place baking dish on a #baking sheet{}.

Bake "lasagna" on middle rack until cheese melts and filling is hot and bubbling, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> For a browned crust, broil, uncovered, for an additional 2 minutes after baking.

Crush @blue corn tortilla chips{3%oz} in a #bag{}.

Once "lasagna" is done, allow to cool at least ~{5%minutes} before serving. Sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve "lasagna" family style, with @sour cream{3%tbsp}, tortilla chips, lime wedges, and @hot sauce{4%tsp} on the side.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.